item.title: List of All Binary File Extensions (Formats, Types, and Meanings)
item.description: A computer file that is not textual is sometimes referred to as a “binary file.” Some binary file formats, like early Microsoft Word documents, actually save both the document’s text and its formatting information as binary data.

item.title: List of All Text File Extensions (Formats, Types, and Meanings)
item.description: One form of file that may be stored on a computer is known as a text file, and it is structured as a collection of lines of text. Within the file system of a computer, there is a text file that is used to store data.

item.title: List of All XML File Extensions (Formats, Types, and Meanings)
item.description: (XML) Extensible Markup Language is a markup language and file format for storing, transmitting, and reproducing any kind of data. It specifies rules for encoding documents so that they can be read by computers and people alike.
